---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro'
import { SITE_NAME } from '../../consts'
---

<Layout
  title="Sign-in guide"
  description={`How to sign in to ${SITE_NAME}: handle, Bluesky App Password, and alternative PDS providers.`}
  lang="en"
  path="connexion/"
>
  <h1>Sign in to {SITE_NAME}</h1>

  <h2>Your handle, not your email</h2>
  <p>
    {SITE_NAME} signs you in with your <strong>AT Protocol handle</strong> — not your email
    address. Your handle looks like <code>yourname.bsky.social</code>, or your custom domain if
    you've configured one (e.g. <code>yourname.com</code>).
  </p>
  <p class="tip">
    📌 You can find your handle in your Bluesky profile → <strong>Settings → Handle</strong>.
  </p>

  <h2>Create an App Password on Bluesky</h2>
  <p>
    {SITE_NAME} requires an <strong>App Password</strong> — a dedicated secondary password for the
    app, separate from your main Bluesky password. This lets you revoke {SITE_NAME}'s access at any
    time without changing your main password.
  </p>
  <ol>
    <li>Go to <a href="https://bsky.app/settings/app-passwords" target="_blank" rel="noopener">bsky.app/settings/app-passwords</a></li>
    <li>Click <strong>Add App Password</strong></li>
    <li>Give it a recognisable name (e.g. "SkateAT")</li>
    <li>Copy the generated password</li>
    <li>Paste it into the <strong>App password</strong> field on the {SITE_NAME} sign-in screen</li>
  </ol>
  <p class="warning">
    ⚠️ The password is only shown once. Paste it directly into the app without storing it
    elsewhere.
  </p>

  <h2>Alternative PDS providers</h2>
  <p>
    If your account is not hosted at Bluesky, enter your PDS URL in the <strong>PDS server</strong>
    field on the sign-in screen (leave it as-is if you use Bluesky).
  </p>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Provider</th>
        <th>PDS server URL</th>
        <th>Create an App Password</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Bluesky</strong> (default)</td>
        <td><code>https://bsky.social</code></td>
        <td><a href="https://bsky.app/settings/app-passwords" target="_blank" rel="noopener">bsky.app → Settings → App Passwords</a></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Skyware / self-hosted PDS</strong></td>
        <td>Your instance URL</td>
        <td>Via your PDS web interface</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p>
    Any AT Protocol-compatible PDS works with {SITE_NAME}. To self-host your own PDS:
    <a href="https://github.com/bluesky-social/pds" target="_blank" rel="noopener">github.com/bluesky-social/pds</a>.
  </p>
</Layout>

<style>
  h2 {
    margin-top: 32px;
  }

  ol {
    padding-left: 1.4em;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 6px;
  }

  .tip {
    background: var(--bg-alt);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--brand);
    padding: 10px 14px;
    border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
    margin: 12px 0;
  }

  .warning {
    background: #fff8e1;
    border-left: 3px solid #f59e0b;
    padding: 10px 14px;
    border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
    margin: 12px 0;
    color: #7c5700;
  }

  table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: 16px 0;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  th, td {
    text-align: left;
    padding: 10px 12px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  th {
    background: var(--bg-alt);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  code {
    background: var(--bg-alt);
    padding: 2px 6px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.9em;
  }
</style>
